===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Medieval Latin ''[[cranium#Latin|cranium]]'' "skull", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κρανίον]]''' (''kranion'') "upper part of the head, skull".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪniəm|-eɪniəm]]

===Noun===
'''cranium''' (''plural'' '''craniums''' or '''crania''')
#The [[skull]] of a [[vertebrate]].
#That part of the skull [[enclosing]] the [[brain]], the [[braincase]].

